		<title>Dan Benjamin turns it up</title>
		<link>http://www.manton.org/2009/01/dan_benjamin_turns.html</link>
		<comments>http://www.manton.org/2009/01/dan_benjamin_turns.html#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Sun, 04 Jan 2009 23:00:03 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[manton]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Weblogs]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[blogging]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[hivelogic]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.manton.org/2009/01/dan_benjamin_turns.html</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Dan Benjamin did something interesting several weeks ago: he took his popular blog Hivelogic, where he&#8217;s been posting since 2001, and rebranded the content under a new domain, &#8220;danbenjamin.com&#8221;:http://danbenjamin.com/. Apparently that was just the kick he needed to &#8220;get even more serious&#8221;:http://twitter.com/danbenjamin/status/1095227235 about blogging, because he&#8217;s been on a roll lately. A couple of my [&#8230;]]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Dan Benjamin did something interesting several weeks ago: he took his popular blog Hivelogic, where he&#8217;s been posting since 2001, and rebranded the content under a new domain, &#8220;danbenjamin.com&#8221;:http://danbenjamin.com/. Apparently that was just the kick he needed to &#8220;get even more serious&#8221;:http://twitter.com/danbenjamin/status/1095227235 about blogging, because he&#8217;s been on a roll lately.</p>
<p>A couple of my favorite recent posts over there include &#8220;Apologize&#8221;:http://danbenjamin.com/articles/2008/12/apologize and &#8220;Fake Amazon&#8221;:http://danbenjamin.com/articles/2008/12/fake-amazon. The latter is a must-read that finally puts a name to what may be the beginning of the end of the Amazon we all know and love:</p>
<blockquote><p>&#8220;By offering these services, Amazon has created a gigantic marketplace, while simultaneously making even the most obscure or hard-to-find items available to anybody. Just type some text into Amazon search, and you&#8217;ll get results. Lots of results. Too many results, it seems, even for Amazon.&#8221;</p></blockquote>
<p>I&#8217;ve also been enjoying the &#8220;Tack Sharp podcast&#8221;:http://tacksharp.tv/, even though I hope to never pay more than $300 for a camera.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
